{{Infobox Military Conflict |conflict=Third Battle of Elephant Pass |partof=the [[Sri Lankan civil war]] |image= |caption= |date= January 9, 2009 |place=[[Elephant Pass]], [[Sri Lanka]] |casus= |territory= |result=Sri Lankan Army victory |combatant1=[[Image:Coat of arms of Sri Lanka.svg|18px]] [[Military of Sri Lanka]] |combatant2=[[Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam]] |commander1= |commander2= |strength1= |strength2= |casualties1= |casualties2= |notes= }} {{Campaignbox Eelam War IV}} {{Campaignbox Sri Lankan Civil War}}
In the '''Third battle of Elephant Pass''', [[Elephant Pass]] was recaptured from the [[LTTE|Tamil Tigers]] by the security forces of the [[Sri Lankan Army]].
Mahinda Rajapaksa, the president of Sri Lanka declared that Elephant Pass was captured by the army on January 9, 2009.
